<h1>Documentation</h1>

<h2>Paragraphs</h2>
<p><em>Koara:</em></p>
<pre><code>This is a simple paragraph.

Use the return key for lines
that need a break.
</code></pre>

<p><em>HTML:</em></p>
<pre>&lt;<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;This is a simple paragraph.&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;Use the return key for lines&lt;<span class="pl-ent">br</span>&gt;
that need a break.&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;</pre>

<p>If enabled, any default block of text will become a paragraph. Paragraphs are separated by one or more blank lines. 
Koara uses return-based line breaks.<p>

<h2>Headings</h2>
<p><em>Koara:</em></p>
<pre><code>= Heading 1
== Heading 2
=== Heading 3
==== Heading 4
===== Heading 5
====== Heading 6
\= A heading can be escaped like this.
</code></pre>

<p><em>HTML:</em></p>
<pre>&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h1</span>&gt;Heading 1&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h1</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h2</span>&gt;Heading 2&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h2</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h3</span>&gt;Heading 3&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h3</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h4</span>&gt;Heading 4&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h4</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h5</span>&gt;Heading 5&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h5</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">h6</span>&gt;Heading 6&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">h6</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;= A heading can be escaped like this.&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;</pre>

<p>If enabled and a line starts with equal signs, it will be considered a heading. The maximum header-level is 6. Whitespace or blank lines are always optional.<p>
<p><strong>Escaping:</strong> If you don't want koara to parse an equal-sign as a heading, you can escape it, by prepending a backslash. You can also escape 
all other characters used in the syntax.

<h2>Lists</h2>
<p><em>Koara:</em></p>
<pre><code>- Item 1
- Item 2
    - Item 2A
    - Item 2B
1. Item 1
2. Item 2
    1. Item 2A
    2. Item 2B
</code></pre>

<p><em>HTML:</em></p>
<pre>&lt;<span class="pl-ent">ul</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="pl-ent">li</span>&gt;Item 1&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">li</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="pl-ent">li</span>&gt;
    &lt;<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;Item 2&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;
