<h2>Code</h2>
<p><em>Koara:</em></p>
<pre><code>Inline `code` works with backticks. You can also create a fenced code block

```
function greeting() {
  console.log("Hello World");
}
```
</code></pre>

<p><em>HTML:</em></p>
<pre>&lt;<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;Inline &lt;<span class="pl-ent">code</span>&gt;code&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">code</span>&gt; works with backticks.&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">p</span>&gt;

&lt;<span class="pl-ent">pre</span>&gt;&lt;<span class="pl-ent">code</span>&gt;function greeting() {
  console.log(<span class="pl-c1">&amp;quot;</span>Hello World<span class="pl-c1">&amp;quot;</span>);
}&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">code</span>&gt;&lt;/<span class="pl-ent">pre</span>&gt;</pre>